    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's the thing... it doesn't feel temporary. it feels permanent. like the music didn't just stop, it's like it was never there to begin with. i look at my hands and they're just skin and bone. there's no soul behind them anymore. if the light is gone, why do i still have to keep the lamp turned on? it feels so pointless.",
